<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspableObject> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/PhysicalObject> .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspableObject> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A physical object inferred to be graspable because it has at least one grasping affordance."@en .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspableObject> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "graspable object"@en .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspableObject> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A physical object inferred to afford grasping by a robot end effector in the task context."@en .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspableObject> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "graspable object"@en .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspableObject> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#relatedMatch> <http://www.ease-crc.org/ont/SOMA.owl#MovedObject> .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspableObject> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#relatedMatch> <http://www.ease-crc.org/ont/SOMA.owl#Patient> .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspableObject> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "This is a course-level inferred class. It should not be treated as equivalent to a SOMA role such as soma:MovedObject or soma:Patient, because those terms describe participation roles in activities rather than the local OWL classification rule used in this homework."@en .
#
# https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspingAffordance
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspingAffordance> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An affordance by which an object can be grasped, held, lifted, or repositioned by a robot gripper."@en .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspingAffordance> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "grasping affordance"@en .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspingAffordance> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#relatedMatch> <http://www.ease-crc.org/ont/SOMA.owl#Disposition> .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspingAffordance> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#relatedMatch> <http://www.ease-crc.org/ont/SOMA.owl#Grasping> .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/GraspingAffordance> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "The course term is represented locally as an affordance class. SOMA models affordance-like knowledge through dispositions and task-oriented action descriptions; therefore relatedMatch is used rather than exactMatch."@en .
#
# https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/ManipulationTask
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/ManipulationTask> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broadMatch> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#Task> .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/ManipulationTask> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A robot task in which an agent changes the pose, state, or arrangement of physical objects."@en .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/ManipulationTask> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "manipulation task"@en .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/ManipulationTask> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#relatedMatch> <http://www.ease-crc.org/ont/SOMA.owl#Manipulating> .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/ManipulationTask> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "The course term covers the project tasks, including cup stacking, cutlery arrangement, and toy block collection."@en .
#
# https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/PhysicalObject
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/PhysicalObject> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#closeMatch> <http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl#PhysicalObject> .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/PhysicalObject> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A material object in the task environment, such as a cup, fork, toy block, plate, or basket."@en .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/PhysicalObject> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "physical object"@en .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/PhysicalObject> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#relatedMatch> <http://www.ease-crc.org/ont/SOMA.owl#ShapedObject> .
<https://hcis.io/ontology/aicapstone/2026/PhysicalObject> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "The course term is intentionally broad. DUL provides a foundational physical-object category, while SOMA provides robotics-oriented refinements for embodied activity contexts."@en .
